<div class="mw-references-wrap" typeof="mw:Extension/references" about="#mwt619" data-mw='{"name":"references","attrs":{"group":"lower-alpha","responsive":"1"},"body":{"html":""}}'><ol class="mw-references references" data-mw-group="lower-alpha"><li about="#cite_note-1" id="cite_note-1"><a href="./Mongol_Empire#cite_ref-1" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-1" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Karakorum" title="Karakorum" id="mwCQ">Karakorum</a> was founded in 1220 and served as capital from 1235 to 1260.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-2" id="cite_note-2"><a href="./Mongol_Empire#cite_ref-2" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-2" class="mw-reference-text">Following the death of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Möngke_Khan" title="Möngke Khan" id="mwCg">Möngke Khan</a> in 1259, no one city served as capital. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Khanbaliq" title="Khanbaliq" id="mwCw">Khanbaliq</a> (Dadu), modern-day <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Beijing" title="Beijing" id="mwDA">Beijing</a>, was the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Yuan_dynasty" title="Yuan dynasty" id="mwDQ">Yuan</a> capital between 1271 and 1368.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-4" id="cite_note-4"><a href="./Mongol_Empire#cite_ref-4" data-mw-group="lower-alpha" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-4" class="mw-reference-text">Including coins such as <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Dirham" title="Dirham" id="mwDg">dirhams</a> and paper currencies based on silver (<i id="mwDw"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Sukhe_(unit)" title="Sukhe (unit)" id="mwEA" class="mw-redirect">sukhe</a></i>) or silk, or the later small amounts of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Yuan_dynasty_coinage" title="Yuan dynasty coinage" id="mwEQ">Chinese coins</a> and paper <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Chao_(currency)" title="Chao (currency)" id="mwEg">Chao</a> currency of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Yuan_dynasty" title="Yuan dynasty" id="mwEw">Yuan dynasty</a>.</span></li></ol></div></div></div></td></tr></tbody></table><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Pages_using_infobox_country_with_unknown_parameters#p16Mongol%20Empire" about="#mwt8" id="mwFA"/>
